   Corrections &amp; Amplifications
    THE NEW YORK STOCK EXCHANGE will halt trading for one
hour if the Dow Jones Industrial Average falls 250 points.
The Big Board delays program traders' use of its automated
order system by five minutes only if stock-index futures fall
enough to trigger trading limits at the Chicago Mercantile
Exchange. Yesterday's edition misstated the Big Board
restrictions.
